	<div id="p106433" class="post row-fluid even">
	
		<div class="postbody span9">
			

			<div class="author">by <strong><a href="./memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=5229&amp;sid=3833a0829c674a39b40e804876fe5170">prophet36</a></strong> &raquo; Fri Jun 22, 2012 4:21 pm </div>

			

			<div class="content">It would be interesting to see what kind of data throughput is achievable on the RPi. You can try it by making sure you have 300MiB free on your RPi's local filesystem (not on a network drive) and doing a 300MiB read like this:<br /><br />time ./linux.armel/rel/flcli -v 1443:0007 -a 'r0 0x12c00000 &quot;bigFile.out&quot;'<br /><br />...and then writing the 300MiB file back:<br /><br />time ./linux.armel/rel/flcli -v 1443:0007 -a 'w0 &quot;bigFile.out&quot;'<br /><br />I'd expect each operation to take around 15-20 seconds.</div>

			

		</div>

		
