	<div id="p107214" class="post row-fluid even">
	
		<div class="postbody span9">
			

			<div class="author">by <strong><a href="./memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=5229&amp;sid=3833a0829c674a39b40e804876fe5170">prophet36</a></strong> &raquo; Sat Jun 23, 2012 8:52 pm </div>

			

			<div class="content">Hmm...so at least 32/5.468 = <span style="font-weight: bold">5.8MiB/s</span> read throughput and at least 32/1.794 = <span style="font-weight: bold">17.8MiB/s</span> write throughput...not brilliant, but not bad. The results for my desktop PC for the same test are 25.0MiB/s and 22.7MiB/s.<br /><br />You should be able to specify a udev rule so that the OS grants user-level or group-level access to your device. This is covered in section 2.1 of the <a href="http://www.swaton.ukfsn.org/docs/fpgalink/vhdl_paper.pdf" class="postlink"><span style="color: #0000FF">user manual</span></a>.</div>

			

		</div>

		
