			<div class="content">Fpga on raspberry pi? Sounds really interesting!<br /><br />I wonder if anybody have though of making a FPGA 'shield' for the raspberry pi. If possible, could you do the programming of the shield over the GPIO pins?<br /><br />Also would it be possible to do the 'synthesis' of the bitstream in the RaspberryPi itself from VHDL before autoloading to the shield?<br /><br />It sounds crazy to me, but I would love to see the changing of FPGA codes to be an 'sd card swap' away.</div>

			

